name: Organic Traditions Stevia Leaf Powder 100gm
desc: Stevia` also commonly known as sweet leaf or sugar leaf` is a natural sweetener indigenous to the Amazon. For centuries the Guaran�� people of Paraguay` Brazil and Bolivia have used fresh stevia leaves to sweeten recipes` teas and medicinal preparations. Stevia is ideal for anyone on a carbohydrate-cautious diet for although it is one of the sweetest substances in nature` it has one of the lowest glycemic scores with no effect on blood sugar. Organic Traditions Stevia powder contains naturally occurring steviosides. Steviosides are compounds in the leaf that are known as steviol glycosides and are 300 times sweeter than sugar. Although there are extracts that can be made of the leaves and purified for steviosides and rebaudiosides at various percentages` Organic Traditions Stevia powder is the whole food green leaf powder offering these naturally occurring steviol glycosides as well as other beneficial compounds as nature intended.

name: Organic Tradition Chia & Flax Seed Powder 227gm
desc: Organic Traditions Sprouted Chia & Flax seed powder is a combination of both Sprouted Chia and Sprouted Flax seeds. Sprouted Chia seeds are a good source of Calcium and Iron` a high source of Fiber and provide 3 grams of vegetarian Omega-3 per 15 gram serving. Aztec warriors would consume a mixture of Chia and water during hunting trips to ensure stamina and endurance. Flax seeds` also commonly known as Linseeds` have been used as a staple food for thousands of years. They are a good source of Calcium and Iron` a high source of Fiber and provide 3 grams of vegetarian Omega-3 per one heaping tablespoon 15 gram serving. Flax seeds also contain Lignans` which are unique compounds that have been shown to provide numerous health benefits. Flax seeds are mucilaginous in nature and as such provide a soothing film for irritated mucous membranes. These activated sprouted seeds deliver more nutrients per gram when compared to raw` non-sprouted Chia or Flax seeds. The sprouting process improves digestibility and allows for a greater absorption of nutrients. Enzyme inhibitors are eliminated and anti-nutritive compounds such as phytic acid are reduced. The sprouting process not only dramatically increases vitamins and minerals in the seed` it also doubles the antioxidant score (ORAC) making Sprouted Chia and Flax Seed powder not only a nutritional powerhouse` but also more shelf stable than raw Chia and Flax seeds. Sprouted Chia and Flax seed powder contains Omega 3 fatty acids` bio-available essential vitamins and minerals and an impressive host of antioxidants` giving them an ORAC value of 1`600 per 1 heaping tablespoon 15 gram serving. Simply add Organic Traditions Sprouted Chia and Flax powder to everything you eat to reduce the glycemic load of any recipe. This sprouted and coldmilled powder is a fast and simple way to enhance your daily diet with an extra boost of dense superfood nutrition.

name: Organic Traditions Flax Seed Powder 227gm
desc: Flax seeds have been used as a staple food for thousands of years by many cultures. Sprouted Flax seeds are a source of Calcium and Iron` a high source of Fiber and provide 3 grams of Omega-3 per 1 heaping tablespoon 15 gram serving. These activated sprouted seeds deliver more nutrients per gram when compared to raw` non-sprouted flax seeds. The sprouting process improves digestibility and allows for a greater absorption of nutrients. Enzyme inhibitors are eliminated and anti-nutritive compounds such as phytic acid are reduced. The sprouting process not only dramatically increases vitamins and minerals in the seed` it also doubles the antioxidant score (ORAC) making Sprouted Flax not only a nutritional powerhouse` but also more shelf stable than raw Flax seeds. Sprouted Flax Seeds contain Omega 3 fatty acids` bio-available essential vitamins and minerals` an impressive host of antioxidants` giving them an ORAC value of 800 per 1 heaping tablespoon 15 gram serving as well as lignans` which are unique compounds that have been shown to provide numerous health benefits. Simply add Organic Traditions Sprouted Flax powder to everything you eat to reduce the glycemic load of any recipe. This sprouted and cold-milled powder is a fast and simple way to enhance your daily diet with an extra boost of dense superfood nutrition.

name: Organic Traditions Coconut Palmsugar 227gm
desc: Coconut has long been used as a traditional superfood in many cultures around the world. In the Philippines` it is referred to as the tree of life and in India as the tree` which provides all the necessities of life. Coconut palm sugar is one of natures most incredible sweeteners with a much lower glycemic index than conventional sugar` honey or agave. It is the perfect healthy alternative to sweetening any recipe. Delicious caramel nectar is collected from the blossoms of the coconut palm tree` dried and crystallized into fine sugar-like granules with the perfect note of sweetness along with nutritional benefits such as B Vitamins` Magnesium` Zinc` Iron` Potassium and Amino Acids. Organic Traditions coconut palm sugar is sustainably grown` minimally processed and unbleached. There are no fillers` flavors` preservatives` chemical inputs or cane sugar added` just 100% pure coconut palm sugar.

name: Organic Traditions Spirulina Powder 150gm
desc: Spirulina is a spiral shaped green microalgae. One of the most nourishing superfoods known` it contains a host of vitamins` minerals and antioxidants. As a source of high quality` easily digested vegetarian protein` Spirulina offers all essential amino acids along with a unique fatty acid known as GLA or Gamma linolenic acid` an anti-inflammatory compound found in mothers milk. Its vibrant green color is due to the concentration of chlorophyll and the antioxidant phycocyanin. It has been traditionally used to promote alkalinity and detoxification. Organic Traditions offers the cleanest` safest` third party tested Certified Organic Spirulina in the industry. Each batch undergoes rigorous testing in order to ensure that our Spirulina is free of heavy metals` pesticides and other contaminants. Spirulina that is grown in uncontrolled` natural environments is difficult to regulate in terms of microorganism growth and contaminants. Spirulina easily absorbs chemicals and other toxins from the environment and so it is important to choose a reliable source. Organic Traditions Spirulina is cultivated in a pristine` controlled environment` using water that is rich in naturally occurring nutrients and minerals to ensure optimal quality and nutritional value. Unlike Chlorella` Spriulinas soft cell wall is highly digestible and the nutrients are easy to absorb and so no cell wall breakage is required. Organic Traditions Spirulina contains no fillers` preservatives` additives` sweeteners` carriers` stabilizers or excipients.
